params.name: creationCallback
params.description:
- Encapsulate the creation of an object outside
of the object pool to avoid having to access 'arguments' and call apply.

classitems.description:
Represent the current number of of objects not being used.
_poolCount - 1 represents the index of the next object to use on get.
classitems.name: _poolCount

classitems.description: Total number of objects that have been created by the instance of the pool.
classitems.name: _allocatedCount

classitems.description:
Returns a free object if available.
Creates a new object and adds it to the pool if none are available.
Note: The current implementation is to not set any used index to null
to avoid an extra index look-up operation for performance.
classitems.name: get

classitems.description: Adds an object to the object pool for reuse.
classitems.name: put

classitems.description: Allocates new objects for the pool.
classitems.name: expand

params.name: amount
params.description: - Number of objects to add to the pool.
